<paragraph blockId="64.[188,795,1321,1985]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,300,1321,1345]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Comment</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="HLAVAC, P. &amp; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M." box="[318,548,1321,1349]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref77416" refString="HLAVAC, P.; NEWTON, A. F. &amp; MARUYAMA, M. 2011: World catalogue of the species of the tribe Lomechusini (Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Zootaxa 3075: 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="2011">HLAVÁČ et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
list 
<taxonomicName authority="(PEYRON, 1857)" baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[603,794,1321,1345]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Drusilla erichsoni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PEYRON, E. &amp; Myrmedonia Erichsonis PEYRON &amp; In &amp; FAIRMAIRE, L." box="[198,351,1353,1377]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="619 - 647" refId="ref78273" refString="PEYRON, E. 1857: 1. Myrmedonia Erichsonis PEYRON. - In: FAIRMAIRE, L.: Rapport sur la session extraordinaire tenue a Montpellier au mois de Juin 1857. - Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 5: 619 - 647." type="journal article" year="1857">PEYRON, 1857</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as a species incertae sedis and 
<taxonomicName authority="(PEYRON, 1858)" baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmedonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis box="[698,793,1354,1377]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. aptera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PEYRON, E." box="[198,348,1385,1409]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="353 - 434" refId="ref78321" refString="PEYRON, E. 1858: Catalogue des coleopteres des environs de Tarsous (Caramanie), avec la description des especes nouvelles. - Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 6: 353 - 434." type="journal article" year="1858">PEYRON, 1858</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
as a “nomen dubium?”. As can be inferred from an earlier revision of the West Palaearctic species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="LEACH" authorityYear="1819" box="[189,274,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,274,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Drusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[289,413,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[289,413,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
undoubtedly belongs to the nominal subgenus (
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[342,497,1481,1505]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="111 - 149" refId="ref76224" refString="ASSING, V. 2005 b: On the western Palaearctic species of Drusilla LEACH, with special reference to the species of the eastern Mediterranean (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 111 - 149." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING 2005b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[188,795,1321,1985]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[189,384,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[189,384,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Drusilla erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described based on material from the environs of Montpellier; the species is endemic to southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[465,537,1578,1601]" name="France" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[553,710,1577,1601]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="111 - 149" refId="ref76224" refString="ASSING, V. 2005 b: On the western Palaearctic species of Drusilla LEACH, with special reference to the species of the eastern Mediterranean (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 111 - 149." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING 2005b</bibRefCitation>
). In the original description of 
<taxonomicName authority=", PEYRON (1858)" authorityName=", PEYRON" authorityYear="1858" box="[445,725,1609,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmedonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis box="[445,542,1610,1633]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. aptera</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="PEYRON, E." box="[559,725,1609,1633]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="353 - 434" refId="ref78321" refString="PEYRON, E. 1858: Catalogue des coleopteres des environs de Tarsous (Caramanie), avec la description des especes nouvelles. - Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France 6: 353 - 434." type="journal article" year="1858">PEYRON (1858)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
states that the species is “assez commune” in the environs of “Tarsous” (southern 
<collectingCountry box="[414,507,1673,1697]" name="Turkey" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
) and that he also saw 
<specimenCount pageId="64" pageNumber="77" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
from “Montpellier, Près de port Juvénal”. Thus, there is no doubt that the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", PEYRON" authorityYear="1858" box="[631,726,1738,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmedonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis box="[631,726,1738,1761]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. aptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to at least two species. The whereabouts of Peyron´s type material is unknown (
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[492,650,1801,1825]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" pagination="111 - 149" refId="ref76224" refString="ASSING, V. 2005 b: On the western Palaearctic species of Drusilla LEACH, with special reference to the species of the eastern Mediterranean (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 111 - 149." type="journal article" year="2005">ASSING 2005b</bibRefCitation>
). In order to dispose of the doubtful name 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", PEYRON" authorityYear="1858" box="[523,620,1834,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmedonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis box="[523,620,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. aptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male from the environs of Montpellier, where 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[556,681,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[556,681,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only species matching the original description, is designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[255,352,1929,1953]" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", PEYRON" authorityYear="1858" box="[403,500,1930,1953]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Myrmedonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aptera">
<emphasis box="[403,500,1930,1953]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. aptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="PEYRON" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[189,313,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Drusilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="64" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erichsoni">
<emphasis box="[189,313,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="77">D. erichsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
